description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply. This is a fixed term/secondment contract only.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Health Education England (HEE) exists for one reason only: to support the delivery of excellent healthcare and health improvement to the patients and public of England by ensuring that the workforce of today and tomorrow has the right numbers, skills, values and behaviours, at the right time and in the right place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Postgraduate Medical Education Team at Health Education England is a fundamental part of the organisation, taking on the responsibility for the administrative support for recruitment, training, assessment and rotation of doctors and dentists in training across the whole of England, as well as sharing our expertise to support allied health professionals and the regional healthcare providers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to work in a dynamic, challenging and rewarding environment to help support training and education of postgraduate doctor and dentists.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Health Education England, working across West Midlands, is responsible for overseeing and supporting the implementation and ongoing delivery of recruitment, training and education programmes for postgraduate doctors and dentists across the West Midlands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be responsible for supporting the operational delivery of recruitment activities and will take a lead in the end to end management of processes within the online application system including training and advising colleagues as well as supporting applicants and other stakeholders as required. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be required to liaise extensively with a wide range of stakeholders across the UK and will ensure that administrative support, professional communications, processes and procedures are delivered to a high standard. This will be a varied and busy role and so the post holder must have enthusiasm and drive to provide an excellent service to stakeholders and to support the team to deliver against its objectives for recruitment. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Able to work in a fast paced environment, the post holder must have proven high level administrative and project support skills and experience including working with excellent attention to detail and be able to manage a very diverse workload working to tight deadlines. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The ideal candidate should have a degree or equivalent with excellent IT and organisational skills and be capable of providing supervision and leadership to a team. The post holder must have excellent interpersonal and communication skills and be able to use their initiative to work independently with minimal supervision. The post holder must also be willing and able to travel as although based in Birmingham, there will be a requirement to travel within the health economy and nationally on occasion as part of this role. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Previous experience in a recruitment role is desirable but not essential for this post as training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants will commence at the bottom of Band 5 with a full-time starting salary of £24,907, with pay step increases after 2 years’ service and 4 years’ service. These salaries are offered in accordance with NHS Terms and Conditions and the HEE Pay Progression Policy and are subject to annual cost of living review.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you like what you have read and think you have the skills and experience we need then don&#39;t delay, apply today! We get lots of applications for our roles and so we sometimes have to close our posts early. Don&#39;t miss out!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: Applicants from within the NHS will be offered on a secondment basis only, agreement should be obtained from their employer prior to submitting their application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Andrea Alleyne&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Recruitment Co-ordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: andrea.alleyne@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0121 695 2214&lt;/p&gt;
